{{lua|Module:Harvc}}
{{uses TemplateStyles|Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css}}
This template is a citation hybrid that has characteristics of long-form [[Help:Citation Style 1|cs1]] and [[Help:Citation Style 2|cs2]], of short-form {{tlx|sfn}} and of the {{tlx|harv}} families of templates. Its purpose is to provide a method that allows editors to refer to a contribution or chapter in a larger work when more than a few such referrals are required.  {{tlx|harvc}} is not a substitute for a properly constructed citation.

Short-form templates {{tlx|sfn}} and {{tlx|harv}} are often used to link from an article's references section to a long-form cs1|2 template in a bibliography section:
:{{tlx|harv}} → {{tlx|cite book}} <span style="padding:0 1.5em">or:</span> {{tlx|sfn}} → {{tlx|cite book}}
It is not uncommon for a source to have multiple contributors.  When it is necessary to refer to multiple contributions in the same source, repeating all of the bibliographic details in multiple long-form citation templates adds to references-section clutter. {{tlx|harvc}} is designed to hold only the detail necessary to identify a contribution and link to the enclosing work's long-form citation where all of the bibliographic detail can be found:
:{{tlx|harv}} → {{tlx|harvc}} → {{tlx|cite book}} <span style="padding:0 1.5em">or:</span> {{tlx|sfn}} → {{tlx|harvc}} → {{tlx|cite book}}

== Usage ==
The minimal form is:
:<code><nowiki>{{harvc |last=contributor name |year=publication year |c=contribution title |in=source editor/author name}}</nowiki></code>

===Parameters===
{{tlx|harvc}} creates a <code>CITEREF</code> anchor from one to four contribution or chapter author surnames ({{para|last''n''}}) and the value in {{para|year}}. This allows {{tlx|harvc}} to be the target of a link created by {{tlx|sfn}} or {{tlx|harv}} family templates.  From {{para|in{{var|n}}}} and {{para|year}}, {{tlx|harvc}} creates a CITEREF link similar to those created by {{tlx|harvnb}} and {{tlx|sfn}}

: '''|anchor-year=''' – optional, for use for author(s) with more than one contribution to the work; requires CITEREF disambiguator; see [[#More than one contribution|Examples]]
: '''|author-link=''' – optional, title of existing Wikipedia article about the first contributor—not the contributor's website; do not wikilink; alias: '''|author-link1='''
:: '''|author-link''n''=''' – optional, title of existing Wikipedia article about contributor''n''; choose ''n'' to match ''n'' in '''|last''n''='''
: '''|author-mask=''m''''' – optional, replaces name of the first contributor with ''m'' (commonly 2) em dashes; alias: '''|author-mask1='''
:: '''|author-mask''n''=''m''''' – optional, replaces name of contributor''n'' with ''m'' em dashes; choose ''n'' to match ''n'' in '''|last''n''='''
:: '''|author-mask{{var|n}}=&lt;{{var|text}}>''' – optional, replaces name of contributor''n'' with &lt;{{var|text}}>
: '''|c=''' – required, the title of chapter or contribution; rendered quoted in upright font; aliases: '''|chapter=''', '''|contribution='''
: '''|display-authors=''' – optional, defines how {{tlx|harvc}} displays the contributor list; ignored when '''|name-list-style=harv''':
:: {{para|display-authors}} – when empty or omitted, displays all contributor names in last/first format
:: {{para|display-authors|{{var|n}}}} – displays ''n'' contributor names in last/first format; appends et al. when ''n'' is less than the number of contributors included in the template
:: {{para|display-authors|etal}} – displays all contributor names in last/first format and appends et al.
: '''|first=''' – optional, first contributor's given or first name; alias: '''|first1='''
:: '''|first''n''=''' – optional, contributor''n'' given or first name; ''n'' begins at 2 and increases by 1 for each additional '''|first''n''='''
: '''|id=''' – required when {{para|last1}}-{{para|last4}} are the same as {{para|in1}}-{{para|in4}}; otherwise optional.  See [[#Avoiding circular reference|Examples]]
: '''|in=''' – required, surname or last name of first editor or author of the work that includes the contribution; aliases: '''|in1='''
: '''|in2=''' – optional, surname or last name of second editor or author
: '''|in3=''' – optional, surname or last name of third editor or author
: '''|in4=''' – optional, surname or last name of fourth editor or author
: '''|last=''' – required, surname or last name of first author; aliases: '''|last1='''
:: '''|last''n''=''' – optional, contributor''n'' surname or last name; ''n'' begins at 2 and increases by 1 for each additional '''|last''n''=''';
: '''|loc=''' – optional, other location identifier, displays after {{para|p}} or {{para|pp}}
: '''|mode=''' – controls rendered display to match that of adjacent CS1 or CS2 citations; defaults to CS1 style
:: '''|mode=cs2''' – mimic {{tlx|citation}} style (comma separators, no terminal punctuation, static text not capitalized)
: '''|name-list-style=''' – optional, controls contributor name list display style
:: '''|name-list-style=harv''' – mimic {{tlx|sfn}} or {{tlx|harv}} format (one to four last names); overrides '''|display-authors='''
:: '''|name-list-style=amp''' – inserts an ampersand between the last two contributor names
: '''|nb=''' – optional, when set to <code>yes</code>, instructs {{tlx|harvc}} to render source link without parentheses around the year; same format as that produced by {{tlx|harvnb}}
: '''|p=''' – optional, single page number where cited material can be found; aliases: '''|page='''
: '''|pp=''' – optional, multiple page numbers, page ranges, etc where cited material can be found; aliases: '''|pages='''
: '''|ps=''' – optional, sets terminal punctuation; default is full stop; overrides '''|mode=cs2'''; aliases: '''|postscript='''
:: '''|ps=none''' – renders output without terminal punctuation
: '''|url=''' – optional, URL of an online location where the text of the contribution can be found; aliases: '''|chapter-url''', '''|contribution-url'''
: '''|url-access=''' – optional, use when URL links to a source behind a registration barrier or paywall; inserts [[Help:Citation_Style_1#Registration_or_subscription_required|cs1{{pipe}}2 access icon]]; accepted values are: <code>limited</code>, <code>registration</code>, <code>subscription</code>
: '''|year=''' – required, publication year of the work that includes the contribution

===Examples===
====Basic example====
